Taking 21b.tar.gz as an example, the practise routine is as follows:
 1) Decompress the file of 21b.tar.gz.
 2) Compile and link the programs by commands:
    gfortran -O -c paciae_21b.f
    gfortran -O -c parini_21b.f
    gfortran -O -c parcas_21b.f
    gfortran -O -c sfm_21b.f
    gfortran -O -c coales_21b.f
    gfortran -O -c hadcas_21b.f
    gfortran -O -c p21b.f
    gfortran -O -o pcm_21b.e paciae_21b.o parini_21b.o parcas_21b.o sfm_21b.o 
     coales_21b.o hadcas_21b.o p21b.o
 3) Modify the input file of usu.dat according to your wish.
 4) Run the program by command:
    time ./pcm_21b.e
